sql:
SELECT COUNT(employee_id) AS number_of_employees, AVG(anxiety_level) AS average_anxiety_level
FROM mental_health_data
WHERE mental_health_interview = 'Yes';

external_knowledge:
- 'captains of the ship' metaphorically refers to the employees;
- 'sailing through the stormy seas of mental health' pertains to the employees for whom mental health data exists, indicating their engagement or involvement with mental health support systems or services;
- 'the roles they play on board' corresponds to their job titles in the company.

- "storminess" metaphorically refers to anxiety levels;
- "sorrow" metaphorically refers to depression levels;
- "protective canopy" metaphorically refers to companies offering mental health benefits and wellness programs.

